---
import MainLayout from '@/layouts/MainLayout.astro';

const title = "Privacy Policy — Murmur";
const description = "Murmur collects no personal data. Full privacy policy for the Murmur sleep sounds app.";
const effectiveDate = "May 1, 2026";
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-12">
    <header class="mb-16">
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 mb-4">
        <a href="/murmur" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors">← Murmur</a>
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white mb-6">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-zinc-400">
        Murmur collects no personal data. This policy explains exactly what that means.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-zinc prose-invert max-w-none">

      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        Murmur is developed and maintained by Jordan Thirkle, an independent developer based in the United Kingdom. You can reach us at <a href="mailto:jordan@jordanthirkle.com">jordan@jordanthirkle.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. The Zero-Data Commitment</h2>
      <p>
        Murmur operates on a strict zero-data model. The application does not collect, transmit, store, or share any personal information. This applies to all users including children.
      </p>
      <p>Specifically, Murmur does <strong>not</strong> collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Names, email addresses, or account information (no accounts exist)</li>
        <li>Device identifiers (IDFA, AAID, or any similar identifiers)</li>
        <li>Location data</li>
        <li>Audio recordings — the app <em>plays</em> audio; it does not record it</li>
        <li>Usage analytics or behavioural tracking data</li>
        <li>IP addresses or network identifiers</li>
        <li>Crash logs or diagnostic data shared with third parties</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. What Is Stored Locally (On Your Device Only)</h2>
      <p>
        Murmur stores your preferences (sleep timer, favorites) using your device's local storage. This data never leaves your device. It is not accessible to us or any third party.
      </p>

      <h2>4. System Integrations (HealthKit / Google Fit)</h2>
      <p>
        Murmur allows you to synchronize your sleep sessions with your device's native health application (Apple Health or Google Fit). 
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Write-Only Access</strong>: Murmur only writes sleep duration data to these services at your explicit request.</li>
        <li><strong>No Collection</strong>: We do not read your health data, nor do we transmit it to our servers or any third parties.</li>
        <li><strong>Control</strong>: You can revoke these permissions at any time via your device's system settings.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Third-Party SDKs and Services</h2>
      <p>
        Murmur contains no third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs. The app does not integrate with Firebase, Google Analytics, Facebook SDK, Mixpanel, Amplitude, or any similar service.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Children's Privacy (COPPA / GDPR-K)</h2>
      <p>
        Because Murmur collects no personal information from any user, including children under the age of 13, the requirements of the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and GDPR-K are satisfied by design. We do not knowingly collect personal information from any person of any age.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Audio Data</h2>
      <p>
        Murmur is a sound playback application. It plays pre-recorded ambient audio files stored within the app. It does not access your device's microphone, does not record any audio, and does not capture any biometric or voice data.
      </p>

      <h2>7. In-App Purchases</h2>
      <p>
        Murmur offers an optional "Murmur Pro" lifetime upgrade. All payment processing is handled exclusively by Apple (App Store) or Google (Google Play). Murmur does not receive, store, or have access to your credit card or payment information.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Because we collect no personal data, there is nothing to access, correct, export, or delete. If you have questions or concerns, contact us at <a href="mailto:jordan@jordanthirkle.com">jordan@jordanthirkle.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        If the app's data practices change, this policy will be updated and the effective date below will be revised. The zero-data commitment is a design constraint, not a marketing claim — any change that introduces data collection would represent a fundamental architectural shift and would be communicated prominently.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Jordan Thirkle<br />
        <a href="mailto:jordan@jordanthirkle.com">jordan@jordanthirkle.com</a><br />
        <a href="https://jordanthirkle.com">jordanthirkle.com</a>
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500">
        Effective date: {effectiveDate}<br />
        Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { month: 'long', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' })}
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
